		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,

I got extremely sick on vacation about 9 years ago and was rushed to the hospital. They removed my gallbladder and appendix, saying it "had to be taken out for me to get better". I didn't know any different, so I agreed.

Since that time, I have become a faithful user of your SuperFood, workout 5-6 times a week and just finished my first Bowel Detox last month. I am generally healthy, so the annual Detox program you have laid out is one I have signed up for.

Even though I have had issues at times with gas, bloating and indigestion, I had never really researched about the effects of no gallbladder until yesterday. 

Around November of last year, before I knew about all your products, I bought and tried Garcina Cambogia in capsule form. It had a horrible effect on me as it gave me extremely fowl smelling gas and indigestion. When I learned that you had products other than SuperFood (I had been purchasing it at a local health food store for years) I bought your SuperSlim. Even though I knew it had Garcina Cambogia in it, there were a combination of other herbs in your formula and I figured my issues had probably come from the previous product not being organic or pure. Unfortunately, that wasn't the issue and the SuperSlim gave me an even worse reaction, most likely because it was more potent and pure. 

Given this reaction, I started investigating why I was having a problem and now realize why I sometimes have the gas, bloating, indigestion etc... I also found in my studies that my body is not dealing with fat like it was meant to without my gallbladder and that certain vitamins are not being absorbed efficiently due to the bile production leaking all the time instead of a large amount being added when I eat.

I have yet to figure out exactly why I am getting these reactions from the Garcina. Is it because it is a "fat blocker" and makes my ability to process fats properly even harder? I am also wondering if this is effecting my ability to lose excess fat, as I have been working for two years changing my lifestyle with diet and exercise. I am not vegan and do not plan on becoming vegan but I do eat more vegan foods now that I have found your blog.

Can you please help? I not only would like to know what I can do regarding fat loss but also what herbs I can ingest to help my body absorb important vitamins and process fats properly. Things like Bile Salts, Bentonite, Collinsonia and Betaine are items I found on the web that are recommended for supplementation but are any of these options the best way? 

Respectfully,

Sherry (Elk Grove, CA)
