		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,
Out of the blue I very suddenly started having high blood pressure readings about 3 years ago. After blood tests, it showed my creatinine was elevated.  I was put on 5 mg of lisinopril and have been taking it for @ 3 years now to control the BP. 
During this time my creatinine slowly elevated and got to 2.9.  My doctor wanted to change my meds because he thought the lisinopril was raising my creatinine. After playing with several meds and having horrible side effects I asked to be put back on the lisinopril.  I had none of those side effects from that.  
My doc is confused because I have no other symptoms of kidney disease at all except the elevated creatinine.  About a year ago my uric acid started elevating and he wanted me put on meds for that - I refused. I did some research and tried a few things because I thought the raised creatinine level may be due to an inability to digest a certain kind of protein.  While working on that my creatinine dropped to 2.2 in 3 weeks and my uric acid dropped drastically as well.  
Last week I went in for bloodwork and my potassium was out of range slightly and my creatinine was back up to 2.9, so they asked me to quit taking the lisinopril and come in to repeat the bloodwork.  
I had been drinking an antioxidant drink and been doing your superfood as well. I also had exercised because I am trying to recover muscle mass because it just seems to be going away.  I do not eat much protein but after leaving the gym I did have an egg sandwich. 
My BP is holding about 150/90 - although it's way higher than normal (on the lisinopril) I'm not worrying about it yet.
I was researching what you have said about kidneys and it looks like the kidney tea will flush the creatinine out of the kidneys based on an interview you did many years ago. You said juniper was good for the kidneys and parsley tea will flush the creatinine.  So I am assuming since the Kidney Tea has both in it that would work. 
At this point I am not sure what is going on but no one understands why I have elevated creatinine and elevated uric acid but no other symptoms of kidney disease.  I even went to a specialist in Atlanta.  He just told me I was a weird bird. 
So a couple of questions, will the kidney tea and tincture take care of the creatinine/uric acid problem?  Is it ok to still drink the superfood? I'm not sure of the potassium level.
I am a 58 year old woman and in good health although I could lose about 10 pounds. The only other thing I take are bio-identical hormones. 
Thank you,
Toni Bible 

