		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,
 I'm Annalee.  I have been suffering with severe halitosis and body odor for 2 decades now.  I  have tried special mouth washes,  tablets,  gums,  flossing, scraping  my tongue, detox  programs and even brushing my teeth and mouth every  hour but nothing helped to lessen the smell or the nasty taste in my mouth.  I even visited my gastroenterologist,  he took the matter lightly and even slightly laughed about it.   So that was more embarrassing for me.  I went to see my dentist as well,  but she isn't  very welcoming of the idea and she hurries me up as if she no longer wants to deal with me- that she'd rather deal with another patient.  I don't know what else to do.  I want to enjoy life but I can't because of the constant staring,  people moving away from me,  the facial reactions I see on ce I start talking,  and opening  the window in a  car  because  of the odor that emits  from my mouth and body.  I  want to be well. 
