		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,
Dear Dr. Schulze,
I have always advocated the use of your herbal products for myself, family and friends. You shine in the field of herbal remedies; so with that said, after watching your latest video, "The Truth About Soy Protein...",  as much as I appreciate and respect you as a dedicated herbal medicine practitioner, manufacturer of therapeutic, (high quality) supplements and herbal remedies, I have great difficulty with your promoting the use of soy as a healthy alternative to animal protein. Therefore, I am compelled to ask for your response to my concerns about soy: 1.) Soy contains high levels of phytic acid, and reduce assimilation of calcium, magnesium, copper, iron and zinc; 2.) Trypsin inhibitors in soy interfere with protein digestion and may cause pancreatic disorders...In test animals, soy containing trypsin inhibitors caused stunted growth; 3.) Soy phytoestrogens are potent anti-thyroid agents that cause hypothyroidism and may cause thyroid cancer; 4.) Fragile proteins are denatured during high temperature processing to make soy protein isolate and textured vegetable protein...etc., etc. Source: http://www.westonaprice.org/soy-alert 
There are many other sources that confirm the Weston Price Foundation's claims about re: the health dangers of consuming soy as well. Please reply.
Thanks, 
Donna Mills, Direct Sales Consultant
Neal's Yard Remedies-NYR Organic-US (Ext.)]]></wp:meta_value>
