		<title>Would you enter the arena of breast enhancement?</title>
		<link>http://dev.emizentech.com/herbdocblog/?post_type=Question&#038;p=17394</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Dr. Schulze]]></dc:creator>
		
		<category domain="status" nicename="saved"><![CDATA[Saved]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://herbdocblog.com/?post_type=Question&#038;p=17394</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Dear]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>17394</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date>2014-05-09 13:55:25</wp:post_date>
		<wp:post_date_gmt>0000-00-00 00:00:00</wp:post_date_gmt>
		<wp:comment_status>closed</wp:comment_status>
		<wp:ping_status>closed</wp:ping_status>
		<wp:post_name></wp:post_name>
		<wp:status>draft</wp:status>
		<wp:post_parent>0</wp:post_parent>
		<wp:menu_order>0</wp:menu_order>
		<wp:post_type>Question</wp:post_type>
		<wp:post_password></wp:post_password>
		<wp:is_sticky>0</wp:is_sticky>
								<wp:postmeta>
		<wp:meta_key>mf_post_question</wp:meta_key>
		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,

First, I would like to thank you for the help I’ve received over the years from your many different products. They have assisted me in caring for my husband and five children, mostly without doctors. We are grateful for that.

By brief introduction, I am a 48 year old woman with a short background to share on the subject of breast health.

Approximately 14 years ago, after I had been finished breastfeeding the last baby for over a year, I sought a solution for the dismal condition I found my breasts in. I wanted to cry every time I glanced in the mirror after stepping out of the shower. I had always been an A cup, but now I felt like I had two tiny, empty tube socks hanging from my chest. It was very demoralizing. I searched online and found a company called Mountain Top Herbs that advertised herbal, all natural breast enhancement capsules that were effective in restoring or improving breast size and health. I purchased them and used them, following the directions exactly. I soon began to feel tingling, tenderness and growth! I remained on the formula for about four months and during  that time I regained firmness and fullness. I still have an A cup but was pleased to have some of my former size and shape restored.

Fast forward 11 years or so. I began to feel that my breasts were beginning to sag some and lose firmness. Of course, I realized that this was a normal part of aging, but I wondered if using the same herbs again would produce a similar result. I ordered a six month supply and began taking them again. I did experience some of the same sensations as before, but any firmness or fullness seemed to disappear as my monthly cycle progressed.

After the six months, sadly there was no change in my breasts, even though I did feel better overall while on the formula. It seemed beneficial in hormone balance and female health.

Within six months, I decided to try a product from another company. To shorten this story, I did this a total of four times over three years with the same result each time. Finally, after once again deciding it was useless, that I couldn’t afford to spend any more money and that I just needed to be ok with what is, I thought of you. After all, your products have proven to be the most effective we have ever used.

So, my question is have you or do you intend to create a formula that addresses this particular concern? It seems to be a very big business and the various companies are all advertising the thing that you do best; natural, herbal products for a specific physical improvement. Could you? Would you enter the arena of breast enhancement?

I haven’t yet experienced any noticeable symptoms of menopause, but I wonder if my age is what prevented improvement, or were the formulae just weak? At any rate, I would have to assume my window of opportunity must be closing.

At this point I’m sure you must think me very vain, and perhaps I am. I care for an elderly couple who have become a wonderful part of my life. She is kind and generous and beautiful in every way. Every day though, I see her breasts hanging forlornly down to her waistband and think, “Do mine really have to look like that in 25 years?”

For women, our breasts are such an important part of our femininity and are so closely tied to our self-awareness. I know life can be happy, fulfilling and wonderful, regardless what type of breasts we have. It’s a choice, an attitude. I just want to be the best I can be.

Thank you for your time and I hope if you have any input, you will share it with me.

Sincerely,]]></wp:meta_value>
		</wp:postmeta>
				<wp:postmeta>
		<wp:meta_key>mf_post_q_from</wp:meta_key>
		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Debra, O, Kalispell, MT, United States, deboftedahl@gmail.com.]]></wp:meta_value>
