		<title>DO THE AMERICAN BOTANICAL PHARMACY&#039;S PLASTIC LIDS CONTAIN BPA???</title>
		<link>http://dev.emizentech.com/herbdocblog/?post_type=Question&#038;p=17456</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Dr. Schulze]]></dc:creator>
		
		<category domain="status" nicename="saved"><![CDATA[Saved]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://herbdocblog.com/?post_type=Question&#038;p=17456</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Dear]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>17456</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date>2014-05-14 14:29:27</wp:post_date>
		<wp:post_date_gmt>0000-00-00 00:00:00</wp:post_date_gmt>
		<wp:comment_status>closed</wp:comment_status>
		<wp:ping_status>closed</wp:ping_status>
		<wp:post_name></wp:post_name>
		<wp:status>draft</wp:status>
		<wp:post_parent>0</wp:post_parent>
		<wp:menu_order>0</wp:menu_order>
		<wp:post_type>Question</wp:post_type>
		<wp:post_password></wp:post_password>
		<wp:is_sticky>0</wp:is_sticky>
								<wp:postmeta>
		<wp:meta_key>mf_post_question</wp:meta_key>
		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,
When I've asked if the American Botanical Pharmacy uses plastic lids for its formulas which contain BPA, I have been referred several times to Dr. Schulze's recent blog.  However,I would very much appreciate knowing where in this blog Dr. Schulze specifically states that the lids which the American Botanical Pharmacy uses do not contain BPA.   He states that "there is no BPA in any of my formalas," but it isn't his formulas we are concerned about.  He explains that he carefully uses glass for his bottles and his droppers, but it isn't his bottles and his droppers which we are concerned about.  He tells us that he uses laboratory polyseal caps which are nontoxic, but again, this is not a statement that his lids contain no BPA.  Most parties consider BPA to be nontoxic.  The customers of the American Botanical Pharmacy are actually an intelligent group of people, and nonanswers might not, in some cases, fill the bill. Eventually the nonanswers might instead add up to an unsatisfactory answer. We're probably beyond that point now, but I'm a cockeyed optimist so I'm asking again.  DO THE AMERICAN BOTANICAL PHARMACY'S PLASTIC LIDS CONTAIN BPA??? 
]]></wp:meta_value>
		</wp:postmeta>
				<wp:postmeta>
		<wp:meta_key>mf_post_q_from</wp:meta_key>
		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Pamela, N, Arapahoe, CO, United States, pamelanolan@hughes.net.]]></wp:meta_value>
		</wp:postmeta>
				<wp:postmeta>
		<wp:meta_key>mf_post_date</wp:meta_key>
		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[20140513]]></wp:meta_value>
