		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,
 
I have a question about your Superfood, which I love. I have been found to have a genetic situation (a "glitch" on the MTHFR gene--C677T) which means that I cannot have synthetic B vitamins, particularly not folic acid but also B12 or B6. I have to have the active form.  The synthetic, which I know you would not like anyway, is toxic when one has that genetic situation.  

I told the ND I consulted that I liked Superfood as a source of B vitamins.  She said that ALL yeast products are fed synthetic B, no matter how natural they are said to be. I said I believed yours would not be.  I am right, am I not?  I can't imagine you include anything synthetic at any stage of production. I'd like to go back and tell her!  

The solution to my genetic anomaly is just to eat good food, basically, and avoid any synthetic B.  I can add the right kind of active B, which takes care of various potential risk factors.  I feel that a circumstance like this can propel us toward better health, not worse!

Thanks for all you do.

Genie
