		<item>
		<title> Fan</title>
		<link>http://dev.emizentech.com/herbdocblog/?post_type=Question&#038;p=17709</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Dr. Schulze]]></dc:creator>
		
		<category domain="status" nicename="saved"><![CDATA[Saved]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://herbdocblog.com/?post_type=Question&#038;p=17709</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Dear]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>17709</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date>2014-06-02 12:08:31</wp:post_date>
		<wp:post_date_gmt>0000-00-00 00:00:00</wp:post_date_gmt>
		<wp:comment_status>closed</wp:comment_status>
		<wp:ping_status>closed</wp:ping_status>
		<wp:post_name></wp:post_name>
		<wp:status>draft</wp:status>
		<wp:post_parent>0</wp:post_parent>
		<wp:menu_order>0</wp:menu_order>
		<wp:post_type>Question</wp:post_type>
		<wp:post_password></wp:post_password>
		<wp:is_sticky>0</wp:is_sticky>
								<wp:postmeta>
		<wp:meta_key>mf_post_question</wp:meta_key>
		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,

I cannot begin to tell you how much I appreciate your amazing gift for healing.  You have a special way of seeing through people and circumstances to help us to accept the wonderful health that is ours for the choosing.  It is a powerful testimony to watch people I love and care for put your healing formulas on the shelf as they hoard the toxic pharmaceutical drugs as others seem to savor every ounce of their being way overweight.  After having to watch the irrational list of meds doctors forced upon my Mother the last few years of her life, I am determined to get T-shirts printed up for all retirement centers that say:

DARE TO SAY NO TO PRESCRIPTION DRUGS!  

With a subtitle that estimates the approximate percentage of heroin addicts that started their addict career with a medical prescription from a doctor who knew the risks all too well.  I was actually threatened with arrest if I attempted to intervene the night my Mother's life was taken.  Such threats were not uncommon in my work, along with unfounded and illegal political banning activities.  I chose to stay by Mom's side in lieu of being arrested or barred from seeing her due to an attempt to demand they stop feeding her narcotics every hour insisting they did not want her to be in pain.  They would wake her up every hour and ask if she was in pain.  She would tell them she was not in pain and that she did not want any narcotics.  They would then force her mouth open and force the narcotic under her tongue.  It was really more than I could handle.  When they insisted they were going to get another narcotic to allegedly relax the lower lung muscle, I warned that she needed her lung muscle to remain strong while she had pneumonia so she could breath.  They said they were out of that narcotic at midnight or so.  

She nearly survived the night.  They came in about 4:10 am with the second narcotic.  Thirty seconds after they administered the second drug against her wishes, she stopped breathing. I might have been able to revive her, but the nurse stood in the way until I finally asked her to please leave us in peace.  There are other details of their obvious intent to steal Mom's right to live, but I think you get the idea.  I finally got them to stop giving her Fasomax at 5 am allegedly for bone density.  They knew it could perpetuate dementia.  But, instead of giving her something healthy they gave her expensive dementia meds.  Then, they gave her Lyrica to alleviate the dementia allegedly and then her arms broke out and she had terrible indigestion.  They had the audacity to insist she didn't care when she sometimes went without her oxygen.  She did not need oxygen until they gave her a biopsy to allegedly determine what type of pneumonia bug they were dealing with.... I refused to sign the surgery release, and they failed to warn the DPA that the anesthesia would likely result in further dementia.  A friend at church said his Mother became incoherent after she had surgery due to the anesthesia. The surgery was $25,000 when all the extra days in the hospital were counted in with the medications.       
However, we could not afford the Super Foods and Echinacea.  

The tendency to attack venerable people like this is beyond my understanding, however I have seen similar toxic behaviors in my work as the Founder & CEO of two Solar Architecture firms since 1992.  In 2000, Clint Eastwood had to call a meeting with California Governor Davis to be paid his contracted incentives for a solar system installed on his Tehama Golf Course in Monterey.  At that time, I was in an energy agency proceeding before the California Public Utilities [CPUC].  I more fully realized what I had felt for some time being that humanity must change the way we think about energy deployment to succeed in the needed transformation of commerce. If they would not pay Clint Eastwood his contracted incentives, who would they pay?     

That question led me to found the Kansas Solar Electric Co~operatives, Inc. and The K-SEC Model with the goal to install 1,000 MWp BI-PV Solar At-A-Time to timely achieve a meaningful amount of solar electricity in the market. The K-SEC Model does not sell our solar systems, our goal is to produce --much like your tinctures, and to install, monitor and maintain our solar systems for fifty years.  I was quite pleased to hear SolarCity a firm founded in 2008  are doing a similar for-profit program in twenty-five states.  Their total goal is much lower amount per state than K-SEC.  However, my 1,000 MWp $3.5 Billion goal will provide only about 7% of the 33,000 GWh we presently consume in Kansas.  Scale of deployment or momentum is the primary barrier we face.  I prefer fully integrated solar systems, but SolarCity has followed my prescription to the 'T'.  There is plenty of work for them and their competition.    

You can read about the pathway of discovery I have followed as I have worked to bring more  Solar Architecture into the mainstream market since  1992.  The Kansas Solar Electric Co~operatives, Inc. was founded in January 2005.  That year I also released the first edition of my book "ElectriCity BEYOND THE CURVE OF DEREGULATION".  Read excerpts at this URL:  
www.BI-PVSolarArchitecture.com/TIME-LINE 

I could not have survived all of that stressful activity with all night writing sessions without the work you have done to make quality health products more accessible and better understood with the aid of your books and blogs.  Beets for the blood was quite valuable.  It was not until 2008, that I discovered your work and wonderful products with great books and healing affirmations.  

The fascinating part of this true story is that it was not in Southern California where I lived from 1996 to 2004 that I came upon your work.  In fact, it was in my hometown of Yates Center, Kansas where I live at this time.  The elder man I worked for in 2008 had a home filled with medical bulletins from a variety of sources.  He had the entire series of your original videos and booklets.   I lived and breathed those books on a daily basis for a year or more.  And, still do read them.  Martin passed away only three months before his 100th birthday.  He deteriorated significantly after his family moved him to a retirement center at the age of 97.  When I took him a birthday cake for his 97th birthday someone asked me if I meant 79 -he really looked younger.  

As someone who has studied architecture and the design of environs, I believe our surroundings can greatly impact our health almost as much as nutrition. I have a wonderful little townhouse to live in and I am working on finding a home to purchase.  I am living in the neighborhood where I lived as a child.  I have a goal to help restore the community theater.   

Although, I had always eaten pretty healthy and used curry to keep my blood pressure under control, it was not until I saw your videos that I began to understand how bad even the vitamin and supplement industry really is.  My favorite part of your videos is where you have an entire grocery cart in your kitchen full of vitamins and supplements to help encourage your students to read the labels because most of those products are worthless.  

To balance my life, I have been exploring lavender farming.  The largest of the two lavender farmers in Kansas indicated that he had over 1,000 people at his open house last year many of which were from six surrounding states. 

In closing, I want to share a beauty and health tip I discovered quite unexpectedly.  I only use coconut oil or olive oil on my skin.  My eyes are very sensitive to most cosmetic products except Evan Healy.  Even if I put the skin product only on my hands it finds its way into my eyes.  One day I was out of oil for my face and had a few sun spots on my cheeks and by one eye.  Something compelled me to use the banana peel from breakfast that was sitting on the sink to cleanse my face.  It smooths the skin and the spots on my face are now nearly gone.  That tip is shared with an apology that my resources have been very challenged.  I was laid off work in January.  Why I need to work in a factory with my skills and knowledge is another mystery to me that I work to remedy or finance on a daily basis with minimal returns. 

I think there is a need for an attitude adjustment similar to a chiropractic treatment.  Something needs to be relieved or straightened to allow resources to move through my life with a healthier and more balanced consistency.  I have been displaced so much in the past ten years that it is truly amazing I have managed to keep what I have.  One of my aspirations is to assure my work and the work of other women is recorded.  Thus, I tend to keep more than I may need to.  Although, I am good at stimulating trade, I am having trouble figuring out how to be paid for those results.  I have a healthy appetite, but it is almost as if I have financial anorexia.  I need money so badly at times that I spend it very quickly generally because I need to, but sometimes it seems like it is because I do not care to have it around to worry about.  It may be related to an incident where I was almost killed when a man came into my home and injured me with a piece of steel rebar putting a dent in my skull.  

As I stood there with blood pumping out of my head, I asked him what he wanted.  He said he wanted $100 or he would kill me. I instructed him to stay two feet away from me while I cleaned the blood out of my eyes so I could see to find him something of value.  We managed to keep a peaceful rapport after the initial injury and I gave him a compact stereo he could carry that was worth well over $100.  I suggested as I opened the back door to let him out that he find a safer profession before he encountered the wrong person.  He stood there and paused with the bloody rebar and compact stereo in his hands.  He told me he had been really wanting to go back to school.  

A few years before, I had traveled alone through Europe and Scandinavia for six months with very little trouble.  Anyway, I apologize for having to suspend my Super Foods account until my resources begin flowing again.    

I enjoy your books and find them very inspiring.  Thank you, Dr. Schulze!
 
Eileen M. Smith, M.Arch. 
Yates Center, Kansas 
(620) 625-2015
   



    
