								<wp:postmeta>
		<wp:meta_key>mf_post_question</wp:meta_key>
		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,

I had been eating a very healthy raw organic vegan diet for 2 years after a lifestyle of the Standard American Diet 0f 30 years, though I did shy away from proccessed foods as much as possible.  I had a reaction that I believed to be from eating too much salt, I ate bananas and abstained from salt and ate my raw organic vegan diet until the symptoms of skin flushing subsided. Also at various times when I would go to lay down at night I over the years during my less than optimal eating habits would have a sensation of slight pressure start at the back of my head near my neck that would travel around the left side of my head to the top and then spread down around and into my head. I had no idea what it was, I thought it was an energy thing? Life took a turn and it was easier and cheaper to eat take out food and pizza, still no meat. Well after going on business trip for several months not having access to healthy foods I was eating vegetarian food take out, undon noodles, a few burgers here and there, pizza, prepared non organic food etc. The last straw was when I ate 2 Hershey's bars before bed. I went to lay down only to start to have my floating head sensation this time was different though as it was followed by palpitations in the center of my chest, strong ones that scared me. The palpitations went crazy for several minutes followed by sever tremors. This finally stopped but started once again after a while when I got up to go to the bathroom in the middle of the night. I thought I had a heart attack. I went to the hospital 36 hours later because I was still having tightness in my chest and discomfort in my left chest muscle. The ER doc said no heart attack and sent me home. After researching my issues I found that it must have been MSG poisoning. So I found all the ingredients that have hidden msg and cut them out completely I was still having restless nights trying to sleep. After more research I find that I am reacting to Glutamate in my diet, namely peanut butter for desert. So I cut out all glutamate and that seemed to help for a few days but now I am reacting to eating plain white peeled potatoes and cabbage. So back to google to find out what is causing my food intolerance because there are many people with the same issues and they just can not eat glutamate anymore, issues have causes and causes can be addressed to relieve the problem. Now it seem that I am suffering from leaky gut. Which from what I can tell is only going to keep getting worse and the foods I can not eat growing and disease is sure to follow. Now I fell off my diet hard...I ate conventional produce, lots of sugar in the form of candy bars, ice cream, baked goods, you name it. So heavy metals from the pesticides, wheat, gluten, dairy, a few hamburgers french fries pizza you name it.

What can a person do to heal leaky gut? There is so much conflicting information on the net it is really hard to find a course of action to take. 

I am really resonating with the Dr. William Donald Kelley means of recovering your health with enzymes, black strap molasses, coffee enemas to regain your ability to absorb vitamins and minerals from food but it seems I should be doing something to heal my leaky gut first. http://www.whale.to/cancer/k/lecture.html

I would so appreciate any input you can share on healing a leaky gut Doc.

Thank you so much for your time and consideration with this matter my friend!

Best wishes and warmest regards!

Sincerely,

Justin]]></wp:meta_value>
