Dr. Schulze, it is becoming increasingly difficult to keep silent. We share an office in the house (where I work full-time) which doubles as a workout room with a treadmill and recumbent bike. I have tried to throw hints by opening up windows while she's working out, but its beginning to feel like I'm being rude. There is an intense smell that flows throughout the entire second level of the house, because she finishes her routine by moving to the loft area to do crunches and ball exercises on the oriental rug. The kids say nothing, but soon they're off to school and I'm left to bear it until she showers and leaves for work. Let's not talk about the laundry basket smell!

Listen, I know I'm not perfect, and I don't even know why she puts up with with my chunky butt. But honestly, I'd rather be in a different zip code during her work-outs, because the lingering lemon/vinegar, musk-like smell lasts for hours. What's most interesting to me is that I do not detect putrid perspiration during intimacy – that's when her perspiration seems normal.

Primarily, I am concerned about my wife's health– as there must be something going on internally. I am looking for answers and a way to offer a solution gently before this rears an ugly head. Willing to listen to any advise you can offer.

Thanks!]]></wp:meta_value>
