I have written before about my son who is 21 years old.  He has suffered with bowel issues his whole life. As a baby, his poop was like little sand balls. He was always constipated and I would have to give him enemas to help him go. He would hold his poop as a child because it was so painful for him. I don't know what kind of damage this caused to the muscles in his bowels, but it became harder and harder for him to poop and longer in between. I tried the doctor route, they gave me big pills to give him or mineral oil or stuff to sprinkle on his food, but nothing they gave him helped. He would go a week or so with no bowel movement and finally have a hard and painful movement. It was heartbreaking to watch him. When he was about 8 years old, he became very sick and a friend took us to a retired nurse who did colonics out of her home. It took all night but she cleaned him out and gave me a bottle of your Formula 1. I feel your formula  saved my son's life. It was the first thing we tried that worked.  Without Formula 1, I don't know what we would have done over these past 12 years.   He still needs to take a Formula 1 Capsule each day, but if he does, most of the time he can have a normal bowel movement. He has to watch what he eats and sometimes has to double up on pills, but thankfully they have kept him going. 

Recently, he has been having severe pains in his lower back and abdomen . One attack was so bad he was bent over and couldn't breathe, so he went to the emergency room. They did x-rays and found nothing visible but told him he needs to see a gastrologist and have a colonoscopy immediately. They tested his urine for kidney stones and said nothing there. They made him feel terrible that he had only been taking a herbal formula and had not seen a doctor sooner. He said they frowned when he said Herbal Formula.  

I take your formulas and read all your literature. I have had my son do the 5-day colon cleanse again and he is still experiencing pain. I am worried out of my head about my son having an colonoscopy. I feel it will do more harm than good but am worried there may be some kind of  a blockage in his bowels that could be causing these horrible pains. 

What do I do at this point. I have read your blogs and searched for answers, but don't know what to do to help him. I don't want to go the doctor route.
The doctor he saw at the emergency room has convinced him he is sick, has terrible bowel issues and needs to be under the care of doctor. I pray you will read my letter and advise. 

Thank you.  Julie Rigby]]></wp:meta_value>
