		<title> Odd child</title>
		<link>http://dev.emizentech.com/herbdocblog/?post_type=Question&#038;p=18142</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Dr. Schulze]]></dc:creator>
		
		<category domain="status" nicename="saved"><![CDATA[Saved]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://herbdocblog.com/?post_type=Question&#038;p=18142</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Dear]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>18142</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date>2014-07-01 08:49:01</wp:post_date>
		<wp:post_date_gmt>0000-00-00 00:00:00</wp:post_date_gmt>
		<wp:comment_status>closed</wp:comment_status>
		<wp:ping_status>closed</wp:ping_status>
		<wp:post_name></wp:post_name>
		<wp:status>draft</wp:status>
		<wp:post_parent>0</wp:post_parent>
		<wp:menu_order>0</wp:menu_order>
		<wp:post_type>Question</wp:post_type>
		<wp:post_password></wp:post_password>
		<wp:is_sticky>0</wp:is_sticky>
								<wp:postmeta>
		<wp:meta_key>mf_post_question</wp:meta_key>
		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,

I have an eleven year old son who I am trying so hard to steer away from pharmaceuticals.  He was born sunny side up and I had to push for about 7 hours.  Many doctors have pointed to this for his "brain" challenges.  

He is  socially awkward, but is starting to come around a little.  He used to never look anyone in the eye and would not talk to anyone he didn't know very well.  He was very shy, and while he is making some progress, he is still introverted and has trouble in certain social situations.  At home, he is aggressive physically and verbally and even more so when he feels hyperactive.  When he gets angry he says and does things he doesn't mean.  He is a very bad listener and doesn't read people or situations well.  He has trouble in school as he has a poor working memory and attention issues.  He seems to need to hear and see material over and over to actually grasp it.  He sometimes hums or yells silly things out.  I have always thought he was just being annoying, but of late am starting to wonder if he can help it and if he may have an undefined aspergers/autism of some kind.  He is very self conscious and, at times, I have felt he was depressed.  He eats healthy for the most part.  He eats a lot of fruit and some veggies (more on the non-green side, unfortunately) and low meat....  He exercises a lot with a variety of team sports and swimming.  The only other thing that sticks out to me is that once I stopped breastfeeding at 6/7 months he had a really hard time with formula and I wasn't as educated as I should have been.  We tried about 4 different formulas with them giving him eczema or rashes until finally our doctor told us to try soy and he was on that for 9-11 months until he stopped having a bottle.  I often feel like his brain is "crying out" for some balance and I just don't know how or what to give him to help.  I have tried fish oil,  low sugar diets, sound therapy, a variety of behavior strategies as home, and tutoring for classes.  As I am faced with how to handle this child as he gets older, I worry about keeping control of him as a teenager and his behavior, learning, confidence and how he affects all of us in the family as he is very frustrating.  More than that, I see my child struggling and am so hopeful someone may have answers.  His doctor has suggested food allergy testing, ADD medications as well as some behavior/depression medications as well.  Do you have any thoughts on nutritional causes of children with these types of behaviors or ideas on how to help him?  Thank you for your time and thoughts.  ]]></wp:meta_value>
		</wp:postmeta>
