My teeth are full of silver feelings (most of them from the 80’s). I did replace almost all of them on my lower jaw into crowns ( my dentist advised me to do that due to most of my teeth being covered by about 80% percent of fillings and almost no tooth bone left-and he said the teeth can crack). I did that, and this is the 2nd time I suffered from extreme pain after dental work. Last summer the pain lasted almost a month, and this time the pain has over 10 days. Do you advise to people to do crowns when it comes to this, or do you have some other advice? 

Also, if there is a cavity involved or the dentist says that I need a root canal, I always believe there might be some other solution to that. In fact, my sister never had tooth pain, and her dentist did a root canal on a tooth that she never complained about, and ever since then she has pain in that particular tooth. 

We use both of your gum and teeth formula, and oral tonic daily. 

Do you advise us to use on our cavities or root canal problems the same pack you advised the other patients to use for gum problems (formula 2, Echinacea, tooth and gum and Anti I-formula)?

The bottom line is, do you believe in modern dentistry or would you always use alternative treatments?

Thank you so, so much for everything!!

Marija
