 I don't know what causes eczema, but there was something that happened in my pregnancy towards the end of it. I don't feel comfortable to talk about it but I think I have to tell you. Well, the last month of my pregnancy or even a little longer than that, on the outside of my genital area I experienced about the same itchiness that my son has been having for almost 9 months now on his skin. Mine disappeared with the delivery and his started a month later. I tried many things but nothing really worked. I've resisted using steroid creams on him for 8 months (this just made me cry because I had no support from almost anyone with this) and a couple weeks ago I felt I had to give up and started using cordison cream a few times which 'helped' a little. Then his Doctor prescribed another steroid cream which is a little stronger and that had cleared his face in couple of days but a huge purple spots are left on his legs, and some on his arms. He is not really scratching any more but I have feeling as if he is sick in some other way now, as if inside he is not feeling good. Plus, the rash on his face started coming back slowly, and also on a parts of the body where it wasn't before, like his thighs, stomach.. He is not a weak baby, in fact, he's been at the top of the chart in height and weight, and  he is also looking happy baby, except when he is itchy and since I started using the steroid cream on him. Please tell me what should I do next. I'm a good patient. 

Next is my dear mother. She is 71 years old and almost all her life she was perfectly healthy except that her legs started to weaken in her 50's and she's been becoming less mobile each year. Almost 2 years ago she had her left knee replaced and that didn't really help her much. Right now she can hardly walk with the help of walker or someone. 
Her real problems started 6-7 years ago when she complained to a Doctor of not being able to fall asleep easily. Doctor prescribed a tablets for her and she liked them. Next month she asked the Doctor to again give her same tablets and so she did. Month after that she asked for the tablets again and the Doctor told her that she can't do it because those same tablets may cause diabetes. Then they checked my mom's blood and found out that her sugar was very high. That is how her diabetes started, and today she is on 2 kinds of insulin. After that she developed high cholesterol, high blood pressure, indigestion and nauseousness, difficulty breathing, dizzy very often and her head feels heavy almost all the time, strong acid comes to her throat in sleep and almost chokes her, she's been gaining weigh even though she is eating very little. I was going to order the 'Incurables program' package for her from your website, but would still like you to give recommendations. Please give us advice what she should do!

Now myself. I have two main problems: some lymph in my throat (not cancer or tumor), and something in my stomach. 
I came to the US in 2000 and almost immediately started the typical stressful life that most Americans live; work, college, family.. Just a few months later I started feeling some intense sharp pain in my liver area, which wouldn't let me stand straight at all. I had to lay down for couple of hours all curled up 'til the pain was gone. A chamomile tea would usually take the pain away very quickly and completely. That lasted for several months on and off. I had no idea what it was but now when I know the danger of vaccines, I am almost sure that it must had been reaction from some vaccine, most likely Hep B since I know for sure that I had to get one if I wanted to stay here (in the US). I can't remember which other vaccine I received at that time. 
A couple of years later I started seeing blood coming from inside me through my mouth. One time it was so much that I thought it won't stop. At the ER they did the CT scan and found nothing. Blood test didn't show any serious illness. 
So, they just gave me an antibiotic and 'I was okay'.  For some time. Then it happened again, and it kept happening again almost every year at least once, for about 12 years now. Three years ago I took some natural remedies (Lymph Gland Cleanse HY from Nature's Sunshine) and I hadn't seen it for 2 years or more. Well, it came back once more this year, about 5 months ago.
It doesn't hurt, it doesn't give me any warning that it is going to happen.. I just start feeling taste of iron in my mouth and I know what it is. Scary. I think it is something in my stomach though, because I do feel that there is something in my left side of it, the upper part towards the center, right below my rib cage. Sometimes I feel a sharp pain which would make it hard to breath, and mostly it is just dull feeling of sort of pain. Also, since 2 years ago I feel very bloated even if I only drink a little bit of water. I was never overweight and my stomach used to be flat no matter how much I eat or drink. I am almost 41 now. 
Lately, I have started feeling exhausted even from just simple short walk. I have hard time to catch my breath since pretty long time ago but lately is more severe and I feel like I don't have control of the part of my stomach where I am supposed to breath through. 
The other problem is with my throat. About 2 years ago some choking woke me up and in the morning I went to the ER. The CAT scan showed some lymph in the left side of my throat, just on the side of the Adam's apple. The ENT specialist told me that it doesn't look anything like cancer or something 
'serious'. Since I didn't and don't have a health insurance, nothing else was done. When I open my mouth and look at my throat, I most often see that the walls in the back of it are swollen and uneven. I have a feeling that it has to do with my nerves since, I forgot to mention in the beginning, I also have a problem with. I sometimes, and more and more often, feel such a pressure coming from my neck and staying in the back of my head, that I feel my head will explode, or something terrible will happen. I stopped drinking coffee because I noticed that coffee can trigger it too. Sometimes, when the choking in my throat and the pressure in my head and neck feels too much, I take a benadryl tablet and it calms me down a little bit. I was going to order Dr. Schulze's products on my own, but there is so much of it and seems to me like I need almost every single one. Please tell me what should I do and what to order first. I was actually going to order the 'Incurable program' for myself too, but I don't know if that's exactly what I need. 
I know this message is long but you would be helping at least 3 people here.

I also wanted to ask about visiting your clinic. What are the hours or rules?
The reason I ask is my friend who has pancreatitis and her Doctors almost ran out of options while she feels miserable. I told her to go visit Dr. Schulz in his Clinic and she would most likely. I hope to get a reply very soon.

Thank you,
Nilfera Redzic, St. Louis]]></wp:meta_value>
