		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,

My question for you is not so much on the healing side of things, but on the diagnosis. (Yes, I searched in your blog, so please forgive me if I missed it.) Anyone who is tuned in to natural health knows of all the dangers of radiation and the various methods of diagnosing cancer. My mom found a lump in her breast over a year ago.  She then started juicing more consistently and eliminated sugar from her diet. Knowing the dangers of biopsy, mammograms and other tests such as x-ray, CAT scans and Pet scans, she has not had this lump definitively diagnosed as cancer.  She eventually did (reluctantly)have a mammogram and the lump did show up.  But we know that there are many false positives and benign tumors that can show up on these various tests.  Not to mention, some of these methods may cause cancer to spread if present.  At this point, she is highly considering a PET scan as it would seem that might be the most accurate.  Some in the medical profession are wanting her to get mammogram, CAT and then PET scans all of which add a lot of needless radiation when they can't even say for sure what she has.  

Many natural health web sites talk about the dangers of these tests, and they talk about natural healing for cancer. But I have not yet seen any information on what is the best(most accurate and least damaging) way of finding out if breast cancer is truly present.  Women NEED to know this.  But while we're at it, everyone could benefit by knowing what the best method of diagnosis is for any type of cancer.  Also, how often should one get tested to know what their progress is?  Perhaps some of these tests cannot be avoided?  If so, can you tell us the best way to mitigate the damages of radiation and/or spread of cancer? I know Vitamin C is supposed to help with radiation, but how much?  And I have heard that earthing can help also?  Any insight you can give is much appreciated.

]]></wp:meta_value>
