Please please please can you enlighten us parents who have chosen not to vaccinate about tetanus? How do you prevent against it? what do you do with a child who has a bad cut or wound and could be a tetanus risk? what exactly is a tetanus risk? how is it that we are not all dropping dead of tetanus if it is so easy to get? I have heard very scary stories about this and cannot tell you how worried I have been. I know you have a grown son. I know that you would certainly have raised him to be an active young man. Therefore, he would certainly have gotten scrapes and cuts and so forth. How have you handled this as a parent?

