		<item>
		<title>Could H. Pylori be causing Non-Allergic Rhinitus?</title>
		<link>http://dev.emizentech.com/herbdocblog/?post_type=Question&#038;p=18608</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Dr. Schulze]]></dc:creator>
		
		<category domain="status" nicename="saved"><![CDATA[Saved]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://herbdocblog.com/?post_type=Question&#038;p=18608</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Dear]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>18608</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date>2014-09-09 20:19:42</wp:post_date>
		<wp:post_date_gmt>0000-00-00 00:00:00</wp:post_date_gmt>
		<wp:comment_status>closed</wp:comment_status>
		<wp:ping_status>closed</wp:ping_status>
		<wp:post_name></wp:post_name>
		<wp:status>draft</wp:status>
		<wp:post_parent>0</wp:post_parent>
		<wp:menu_order>0</wp:menu_order>
		<wp:post_type>Question</wp:post_type>
		<wp:post_password></wp:post_password>
		<wp:is_sticky>0</wp:is_sticky>
								<wp:postmeta>
		<wp:meta_key>mf_post_question</wp:meta_key>
		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,

I have recently been diagnosed with Helicobacter pylori bacteria (H.Pylori).  Although it is usually associated with stomach ulcers and acid reflux, those aren't issues or symptoms that I currently have. 

I have had Non-Allergic Rhinitus for 5 years -- meaning I don't test that I am allergic to anything but I have chronic itchy eyes, runny nose, itchy throat, sneezing, and congestion.  Nothing seems to work to minimize these symptoms (meds or natural remedies).  In a process to do some testing to further understand what is going on I discovered I had H. Pylori.

The treatment is 2 antibiotics and a proton pump inhibitor, which I'd like to avoid if possible.  What are your recommendations to eradicate H. Pylori? Could H. Pylori be causing my Non-Allergic Rhinitus?

I appreciate and love all that you do for natural health and healing!

Thanks,

Julie G]]></wp:meta_value>
		</wp:postmeta>
