I am 54 years old. I contracted strep throat the summer before last (July 2013). It was not diagnosed at first as I did not have a sore throat. I had a high fever for a few days and enormously swollen glands. One tends to get those swollen glands (lymph nodes) on either side of the neck under the jaw when ill, but this time they were popping out of my neck quite alarmingly. I have never seen anything like it.
I was able to get rid of the fever and fatigue, but the glands were still there a week later. I went to my GP and she did a culture and I did indeed have strep. She put me on a round of antibiotics... which I hadn't taken in many years. 
It is now over a year later, and although my glands have gone down, they are still very large. The right one is about the size of an egg, and clearly visible at all times. The left one is the size of a grape. I have had nearly every blood test available, and scratch tests, and have had them biopsied and they are not cancer.
