		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,

First, thank you for your amazing help over so many years of service to us all! 

Second, our adopted elderly cat with newly diagnosed hypertrophic cardiomyopathy needs your help! 

We don't know how old he his, but we adopted him about 2 years ago when his owner was going overseas, and she said he was over 10 then. He is male, neutered, and on compounded liquid methimazole for hyperthyroid twice a day (we put him on that after we got him. He may have been hyperthyroid before we got him, but we were told it wasn't too too high when we had him tested, and he's in the low-normal range now.) 

A couple weeks ago started having difficulty breathing, so we took him to the emergency room, later to the recommended cardiologist, and they put him on Lasix/furosemide, Plavix/clopidogrel, and Enalapril in addition to his methimazole, and his diagnosis is: Advanced hypertrophic cardiomyopathy, severe left atrial chamber dilation, asymmetrical left ventricular hypertrophy with pronounced posterior wall hypertrophy, maintained left ventricular contractility, mild mitral valve regurgitation, severe left atrial enlargement, pleural effusion secondary to heart failure, hyperthyroidism appears controlled - recent T4 2.5, at risk for recurrent congestive heart failure and thromboembolic disease.

They have twice sucked fluid out around his heart/lungs, over 300 cc the first time, and I think over 200 cc the last time, 12 days apart, and he's been on his new meds for 4 days now, though we're waiting for the compounded meds to arrive in the mail, so we're giving him crushed pills and 1/4 baby aspirin instead of the Plavis right now (they said to) until the Plavix arrives.

I have always appreciated your mentioning the treatment of animals and pets, how your products work for them too, and I'd like to know what you would recommend for our little guy here!!! Since they eat protein, it didn't seem he should be a vegan, and I know you "fixed" your own heart!!!!!!!! This little kitty loves life, everyone says how sweet he is (and he is!), and I would like to heal his heart, Dr. Schulze. (Dehydrating the fluid out of his body and sucking fluid off is obviously not a fix.)

Thank you for helping, Dr. Schulze!  And God Bless You and All Yours!!!

Best,
Mary]]></wp:meta_value>
