		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,
My son, was diagnosed with Crohns disease in 2010 at the age of 14, but in my opionon was not diagnosed properly.
Since he was a baby, the kid has been constipated. As a baby before he was potty trained, he did not go for weeks at a time. Over the years we have tried everything to get him to go with no success. 
He did have ulcers in his small intestine in the ilium area when he was scoped in 2010, but I have to wonder if having stool constantly in his intestines could have produced the ulcers and the inflammation, since they saw no granulomas and is constipated not running to the bathroom with diahrea like most people have with crohns. 
He has always followed a very strict diet, but his senior year of high school he started to eat some things that are not on his diet. In Nov of last year his CRP came back elevated so, we agreed to do a 6 week course of enticort, to get the inflammation down and get him back on the specific carbohydrate diet, that he had been on for the three years prior. Even when on the diet he still wouldn't have a bowel movement for weeks at a time.
The second day into the enticort, he started to throw up violently and was in bed for days at a time. The bile he threw up ate the sealer off the stone floor. The Dr's told me the drug would not do this and that he probably had picked ups a bug and to continue to give it to him.
Week two and three he wasn't throwing up, but when I started to weaned him off the enticort back in bed and throwing up. After he finished the 6 weeks he then got a partial blockage from the drug. I think the last part of his small intestine was inflamed and the enticort goes right to that area and is absorbed into the tissue. Instead of it taking down the inflammation, it made it worse. We had done a CRP before and after the enticort.
I would love to try your formula 1 product, but I am fearful that he may have a reaction to the cape aloe leaf. A few years ago he had a skin rash when he drank aloe and also one time while he was taking Georges Aloe, he woke up with his whole face swollen. His ears and eyes were almost swollen closed.
It was so bad he had to go on steroids.
I just feel if we could get his bowels moving we could maybe in turn get the inflammation down and save him from loosing that part of his small intestine.
Could you please let me know your thoughts.
Very concerned mother,
Brenda 


]]></wp:meta_value>
