		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,
I am writing from Taiwan where my 49 year old fiance recently had a lumpectomy for stage 2 breast cancer and will soon begin 24 weeks of chemotherapy in 3 week increments.  She is also taking some unknown Chinese medicine "potion" that is mixed at the Chinese doctor's office approximately every week.  (Note: Taiwan has a dual medical system of traditional Chinese practitioners and also western-style medical providers.  Apparently each has agreed not to speak badly about the other in order for both to be covered by Taiwan's national healthcare system.)  She is very healthy otherwise and very active having more energy than most people her age.
I am mostly vegetarian and I have been using your cleanse and detox products for years but I never had any specific health condition requiring more support.  I believe in natural remedies over pharmaceutical solutions and I will never take chemo myself, but I cannot avoid the political issues nor can I dictate what treatment she should take.  She has decided on her own to become vegetarian but much of the anti-cancer diet literature is in conflict.  I am trying to help her choose a diet that will be help to protect her body from the side-effects of chemo.
Many say that all sweet foods, whether from refined sugar or natural sugars, should be eliminated including all fruit--"If it's sweet, spit it out" mentality.  Your literature seems to indicate that at least some fruit is alright.  We crave the mangos, papayas, pineapple and other tropical fruit that is available here.  Also, some say sweet potatoes are good, others say not and I cannot imagine eating a sweet potato raw.
I am returning to Los Angeles in 2 weeks and I plan to stop in your Marina del Rey store and purchase some products including more cleanse and detox products.  Please advise of the particular items that I should obtain to bring back.  I guess I will need a three-six month supply.
Also, please clarify whether some fruit, or which fruits, are compatible with an anti-cancer program and whether potatoes and sweet potatoes are to be avoided or eaten raw.
Thank you.
]]></wp:meta_value>
