My daughter n law to be has 
Fibrous Dysplasia of the Maxillary Bone 

From the little I have read about this disorder I believe it is 
Fibrous dysplasia is linked to a gene mutation that affects the cells that produce bone. The mutation occurs after conception, in the early stages of fetal development. That means the mutation isn't inherited from your parents, and you can't pass it on to your children.

Because it is a gene mutation is there any hope to help heal this condition....
I know you healed your heart problems which was hereditary so I am keeping my fingers crossed.

Thank you in advance.
Yours sincerly

Sharon
