I currently suffer with severe depression and anxiety, and take no medications for any of this. From when I was little, I had a heart murmur, which was said to be innocent and I would grow out of. I question this, but have ignored it for years. However, recently everything has been going terribly and I thought it was my anxiety acting up, but I am now second guessing weather it's a panic attack or something else. I do not usually have panic attacks, but I just assumed it could be that. However, what's happening now is very concerning. I feel a very powerful lightness on the lest side of my upper chest, almost like a wave of stillness, which makes me panic and I do anything I can to get my heart rate up to feel the beat. It's a very odd feeling to describe. It's very powerful, but not heavy or tight. I get  lightheaded, and my arms shake, and the tips of my fingers may or may not pulse and painfully tingle. My arms ache, specifically near my armpits and upper arm muscles, though not terribly, but it's a zap, or pinching strong enough to really worry me. And of course this is all accompanied with crying and shivering which I expect makes it worse.

Lately I've been losing weight unintentionally althought I'm still a healthy weight (135), and my digestive system is normal, but lets say normal still isn't exactly regular. I've been taking the intestinal formula #1 pills for I guess 3 months? On and off though to fit a schedule. My diet has been a mix of all organic, and then bad food when our money is low. I do tend to emotionally over-eat, just saying incase that could be related to anything. I'm sorry to be listing one thing after another, but I just want to be sure I can give as much information as possible. Speaking of which, quite a while ago I was shocked by an electric outlet with a conductor (there was a hairpin sticking out of the outlet that I didn't see and touched),  and my foot in water, through my left arm. Of course no doctor was able to be seen, but I read up that it was no serious danger. I didn't have any concerns immediately after that happened, and felt fine, however now it's worrying me because the source of the pain im feeling is greatly there, and the pain feels somewhat similar.

I've tried to do independent research, but everything is very unsure. Some things say heart disease, and many other very serious things that I flipped out over just reading. Please, please help me. 

So far I use your deep tissue massage oil with a sponge or brush pulling upwards to help circulation on the area, and cough and move around during these phases to try and help the feeling. If you can give me any information on what can help these experiences, as well as even a brief estimate diagnosis, I would be so unbelievably grateful.]]></wp:meta_value>
