		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,
I have been studying your programs for years now, and I have done many cleanses and fasts, and I take superfood daily, but I just can't seem to cure my extreme food sensitivities. I can't eat ANYTHING! Especially fats... even a drop will cause acne eruptions. 

I have been cleansing for years and years, have done many liver flushes, kidney cleanses, and bowel cleanses. At one point in my life, I have even decided to work full-time on my health, and have spent hundreds of hours on experimenting and reading up on natural health remedies. I am extremely dedicated, and worked really, really hard to solve this, but it just doesn't budge. 

I have seen many Naturopath's in the past, and I'm having difficulty 
finding one that can really understand my condition, or one that would
actually care enough to help me solve the issue. No matter how many ND's I see, they are all the same, very science based. Some don't even believe in cleansing, and have told me to stop doing periodic cleanses. They can't seem to go beyond their standard education here in Canada, and seem more like MD's that rely more on synthetic vitamins instead of antibiotics.

Now on the specific issue - I have a very complicated and difficult health issue that seems to be extremely rare. I cannot eat anything other than simple carbohydrates such as rice/vegetables, if I eat any sort of fat or even protein, I will break out in acne on the face and body. This is both painful physically and psychologically. Though I've matured away from most of the psychological pain. The outbreaks occur mostly on my face/back in the forms of whiteheads that I usually have to extract, and I seem to have a lot of hardened sebum on my face. 
  
I had a history of constipation due to terrible diet, and I have done major cleansing of the bowels, including 30 day juice fasts while on IF#1 and 2. Your cleansing programs corrected my bowel movements, and I am very regular now (2 daily). 

Over the years I have been improving my diet heavily. I now eat vegetarian, but my diet is extremely limited, and I seem to breakout from almost anything that doesn't involve carbohydrates. I can't even eat beans or bean sprouts. I am concerned with my health since I'm lacking so much protein and fat. I can't even take olive oil, even a drop will cause eruptions. During my liver cleanses, I will have to endure painful whiteheads the following day. 
The reaction is immediate, it could be within hours, usually 12 or more. 
Thankfully, I can take superfood and juices with no problems.

I am 27 years old now, and I have suffered for over 12 years. I have studied naturopathic medicine for years, and have tried an endless amount of treatments and tests. From the many theories that came up, I believe it is some form of intestinal permeability (LGS) and dysbiosis. A recent ND that I saw administered a stool test that revealed an overgrowth of clostridium spp. I have tried a lot of protocols to fix this issue (anti-microbial/fungal herbs, large amounts of probiotics including lots of raw fermented foods, slippery elm gruel fast etc), but it had no effect on my issue. 

I just cannot seem to end this problem no matter what I try. I really need some help, and I finally decided to try and contact you, one of the most respected doctors I have admired for years. 


I would really appreciate a response thank you!
Jason ]]></wp:meta_value>
