		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,

My name is Gayathri, I am 31 yrs old and married. I recently came to know about you from my friend, after going through so much pain and struggle and 3 emergency room visits.

I have PCOS (Poly-Cystic Ovarian Syndrome). I have been diagnosed with multiple cysts in both my ovaries and I have very irregular periods (once in 3-4 months) and then severe bleeding, cramps and pain during my cycle. And I keep bleeding for a very long time, roughly about 15-20 days minimum. (My highest bleeding record was 72 days). And with my PCOS come a lot of things like - excess facial and body hair, gaining weight, depression, hair loss and receding hair line, etc. I have been on birth control pills on and off.

After I got married 3.5yrs ago we tried to conceive, but I couldn't get pregnant. The doctor gave me Clomid to ovulate because I wasn't ovulating due to irregular cycles. We did Clomid for 3 cycles, out of which, I ovulated twice, but didn't get pregnant. Then she suggested IVF and as we did not have Fertility benefits on our insurance, and did not have enough money to pay for the treatment all by ourselves, we decided not to go for IVF. 

Last year, on the night of October 22nd, I went to emergency room for the first time, due to unbearable pain in my abdomen. They diagnosed that a cyst had ruptured in my right ovary and the fluid was leaking inside, which was causing the pain. They sent me home after giving me pain medication (Hydrocodon-acetominophen 5-325 and Motrin 600mg). It took me 2 weeks to even walk and be normal. Then again in February 4th of this year, I got a similar pain, and went to ER to know that my left ovary was so enlarged to 11.5 cm that it is twisting itself and they had to do an emergency surgery to untwist it. I had the surgery done and was on birth control pills to clear out all accumulated follicles and shrink the ovary. I was on birth control pills for 4 months and then did an ultrasound (in August) and saw that the ovary 
became a little smaller. Then again last month, Sept. 22nd, I had the same kind of pain, but this time was 3 times more than the earlier ones, I started losing consciousness due to extreme pain and went to ER again. This time it was a cyst rupture again, and my left ovary too had enlarged again to 8.5 cm. But this time since they spotted blood flow through my ovary, my OB/GYN doctor said it was not an emergency situation that needed surgery, but suggested that the ovary should be removed otherwise it will keep creating the same kind of issues. And because I wanted to get pregnant, she asked me to go to fertility specialist and said that she couldn't do 
anything else for my pregnancy. She has again put me on birth control pills for 3 months now to shrink my ovary. And she said my ovary would enlarge again if I come off the pills, and might need surgery again.

After going to the ER for 3 times in 11 months, I finally came to my senses and researched about natural treatment online and found that it is possible to reverse my condition and there is hope. Then through my friend I looked at your website, blog and read through all questions and watched almost all videos including your Minimum entry requirements video. 
I have already gave up sugar, coffee, dairy, animal products, even white rice (the main food I grew up on) and now I've started eating raw vegetable and fruits for the past 1 week. My bowels have always been 2-3 times a day. I usually do a good amount of cardio (4-6 times a week). I'm willing to do your detox programs and take super food, female formula, whatever you advice. I 
only have a couple of questions.

Can I take them along with my birth control pills, or should I come off the pills? I'm afraid that my ovary would enlarge again if I come off the pill and I really don't want to go into that room again. Also, it's been only 3 weeks since I went to the ER (they gave me pain medication through IV 3 times because the pain did not come down, and I was vomitting all the fluids out for 2 days after I came home) and 1 week since I stopped taking all those powerful pain medications. When would be the right time to start taking your formulas? What all should I take for my condition and in which order? Please advice.

I have gone through so much pain in the past 18 years and I don't want to struggle anymore. I'm desperate! Please help.
Thank you for all that you do and being there to help us. God bless you!

Thanks,
Gayathri
Dublin, CA
Oct.13th 2014
]]></wp:meta_value>
