		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,

My 18-year old male cat has been very healthy his entire life. In April of this year, he lost use of his hind legs. The veterinarian said he had had a stroke and gave him vincodin, a derivative of the vinca plant. He recovered really well. Five months later he had another, worse, episode ... and lost use of his entire right side. He mostly recovered from that, but with an intermittent limp on his right front leg. 

This week he lost use of his right side again, and now it seems as if he is losing use of all legs. His attitude is great -- he eats and drinks, purrs when I hold him, and pees in the litterbox ... but he requires total care. I have to "intuit" what he needs, and then carry him to the litterbox, etc. 

Yesterday I gave him several shots of your Heart tonic (frothing mouth included). In the night his heart was beating very rapidly, but no changes in his ability to use his legs. Most of his care was in France, where veterinarians don't automatically suggest euthanasia. For the past month we've been in the US, and I'm reluctant to take him to a vet. Do you have any suggestions at all? 

Thank you so much. And thank you for everything you do!

Leslie Elliott


