		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,</p>
<p>About two weeks ago our German Shorthair Pointer, who is 10 years old, was diagnosed with lymphatic cancer. I noticed two very large lumps under her neck and immediately took her to the vet. He gave her some shots and the typical medication and said that she would probably only live from 4 to 6 weeks. She had been very lethargic, not eating much, slept a lot, and was a bit wobbly when she stood up. The lymph nodes were also pressing from behind her eyes so she really looked as ill also. My husband and I were not about to just watch her die, so we went to the local heath food store and purchased Brewers Yeast Powder and Flax Seed Oil. We gave her that at least twice a day. It helped her energy level and appetite and she gained 6 pounds! I was not about to stop with that remedy and thought to order some SuperFood Plus from your store and I also purchased your Detox Formula. My question is: How much Detox Formula should I give her? Is there anything else that I should add to that? Since last Tuesday she has been given a half a dropper three to four times a day. I add it to her food with her Brewers Yeast and she eats it up nicely.
<br>She has so much more energy now that she jumps up in excitement when I bring her food. So far her nausea is nil. I also give her about 10 to 15 SuperFood tablets a day in her food and I know that has contributed to her energy levels. She is the sweetest dog and my husband and I want to do whatever we can to make her as healthy as possible. I would really appreciate any advice on anything else that I can give her and will keep you updated on her progress. Thank you for your time and everything that you do for humans AND animals! :-) 
<br>Sincerely, 
</p>
<p>— Lisa C. in Winston-Salem, NC</p>]]></wp:meta_value>
