		<wp:meta_value><![CDATA[Dear Dr. Schulze,</p>
<p>I am a 60-year-old woman in good health.  Unfortunately, I recently fell down a short flight of stairs and broke my upper right arm.  It has been 7 weeks since then and I am in an arm brace.  Hopefully, in two weeks it will come off and I will start physical therapy. Since I cannot fully extend my arm at this point and the shoulder freezes up quite quickly, I've been told it could take up to a year to get my strength and range of motion back.  I am wondering if your Deep Tissue formula would help loosen things up and speed the process, or is there anything else you would suggest?  I love all the products I've tried so far.</p>
<p>— Cheryl Y.</p>]]></wp:meta_value>
